Date:  0/0/1952
Source:  NZ Forest Glossary
Author:
Vol / Page:
Edition:
Quote:  BREAST-BENCH. A table-high sawbench with a single circular saw and with reversible rollers for feeding flitches in and out. The flitches are set against a fence and the whole rig is designed to give the maximum flexibility in sawing to grade.
